window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>At last, a single volume that gathers together all of the short stories featuring Agatha Christie's most famous creation, Hercule Poirot. </p> <p>The dapper, mustache-twirling little Belgian with the egg-shaped head and curious mannerisms has solved some of the most puzzling crimes of the century - and, in his own humble opinion, is \"probably the greatest detective in the world\".</p> <p>In this complete collection of more than 50 stories, ranging from short tales to novellas, Poirot faces violent murders, poisonings, kidnappings, and thefts - all solved with his characteristic panache. Only Agatha Christie could have devised cases worthy of Hercule Poirot's skill and \"little gray cells\". </p>"; 
